{
  "stem": "19198.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 364.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Miriam was a friend of-- of his.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's how I met her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we met in-- that was actually in-- in-- as I mentioned, in the spring of 1937.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we didn't get married until 1940.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a-- a long courtship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every one of the-- of the five remained, became a citizen, was ordained a rabbi, and played a very positive part in the American rabbinate.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One who was a-- a bit sickly and did not do too well, but was not-- not too sick to become a chaplain.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after his chaplaincy, worked mainly as a [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hallel ?] director.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he died young.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Each of the remaining four became very active in-- in the American rabbinate And each of the-- of the four remaining people held a chair office in the National-- in the Central Conference of American Rabbis, including two who became presidents.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now that's a-- an office in an organization that has about-- what is it?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "About 2,000 or 3,000-- 3,000 members.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The presidency is one of the most important offices in American Jewry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And both the oldest of the group, who has also become a very well-read scholar and a writer, Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Plaut, ?] and the youngest of the group-- one of the two of us who almost didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- those two became presidents of the Central Conference for two-year terms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my colleague who lives right near here, Rabbi Kaelter, and I-- he became a corresponding secretary.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was-- I held the position of treasurer for four years, which is rather unusual because it's-- none of those offices are usually held for more than two years.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we-- all four of us were very successful in the rabbinate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The-- my position here--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was ordained in 1941.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
